14	3	5	12	assistant	Sure! Let's break down the table and focus on **phishing** first.\n\n### Phishing\n- **Description**: Phishing is like a trickster sending you a fake email or message. It looks real, but it's not! The goal is to steal your personal information, like passwords or credit card details.\n- **Example**: Imagine you get an email that looks like it's from your bank. It says, "Urgent! Your account is locked. Click here to verify your details." But if you click the link, it takes you to a fake website that looks real. If you enter your username and password, the trickster now has your login details!\n\n### Other Attacks (Quick Overview)\n- **Malware**: Bad software that can harm your computer, like a virus.\n- **SQL Injection**: A way to trick a website's database into giving away secret information.\n- **DDoS**: Overloading a website with too much traffic so it crashes.\n- **Man-in-the-Middle**: Someone eavesdropping on your private conversation, like listening to your phone call without you knowing.\n\nWould you like me to explain any of these in more detail?	/api/static/audio/tutor_3_5_12_64528.mp3	2026-03-07 15:29:13.149355
