22	1	6	15	assistant	Got it! Let's make this super simple.\n\nImagine AI is like a toolbox. Inside that toolbox, there are different tools for different jobs.\n\n**Narrow AI (also called Weak AI)** is like a tool that does *one specific job really well*. It can't do anything else.\n\nFor example:\n- A **facial recognition tool** only knows how to recognize faces. It can't play chess or drive a car.\n- A **search engine tool** (like Google) only knows how to find information on the internet. It can't cook food or paint a picture.\n\nSo, Narrow AI is like a specialist—it's really good at one thing, but it can't do anything outside of that.\n\nDoes that make sense? Think of it like a robot vacuum cleaner. It's amazing at cleaning floors, but it can't do your homework or walk your dog! 😊	/api/static/audio/tutor_1_6_15_15216.mp3	2026-04-01 16:02:00.907435
